-- India’s Monsoon Rainfall Deficit Narrows to 5%
-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 2012-09-21T13:55:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-21/india-s-monsoon-rainfall-deficit-narrows-to-5-correct-.html
(Corrects spelling of rainfall in the headline.)  India ’s monsoon, which accounts for
more than 70 percent of annual rainfall, was 5 percent below a
50-year average since June 1, the nation’s weather bureau said.  The nation got 798.3 millimeters of rainfall in the June 1
to Sept. 21 period, the  India Meteorological Department  said
today on its website. That is less than the 843.1 millimeters
considered normal for the period, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rakteem Katakey in New Delhi at 
